Class EffectopediaObject

      org.qsari.effectopedia.base.EffectopediaObject

Direct Known Subclasses:
ContextDimension, DescriptionSection, DescriptorUnit, DiscussionPosting, IDs, Lab, Pathway, PathwayElement, PathwaySegment, Reference, ReferenceID
public class EffectopediaObject
extends IndexedObject
implements XMLImportable, XMLExportable, java.lang.Cloneable, Traceable

EffectopediaObject is the base class for all Effectopedia classes that are treated as separate entities and are individually monitored in the EditHistory. The subclasses in the org.qsari.effectopedia.objects package completely represent all the elements of pathways and their components. They also do not override IndexedObject.autoId() and have unique internal (memory) identifier IndexedObject.ID across all org.qsari.effectopedia.core.objects package objects. When EffectopediaObject descendents objects are created they do not automatically obtain new IndexedObject.ID and initially have their ids set to zero. If any of the object fields is modified for the first time the IndexedObject.ID is auto assigned in update(boolean changed, long fieldID) . EffectopediaObject contains also inherits an external file or database identifier IndexedObject.externalID used for matching objects with ones stored in external source.
